					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": "{{base_url}}/todos",
						"description": "Retrieves all todos from the API.\n\n**Method & Path:** `GET {{base_url}}/todos`\n\nThis endpoint returns a complete list of todo objects. The `{{base_url}}` environment variable must be set in the active environment (e.g., `https://dummyjson.com`).\n\n**Response**\n\nReturns a JSON object containing a `todos` array. Each todo object includes the following fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `id` | integer | Unique identifier of the todo |\n| `todo` | string | The todo task description |\n| `completed` | boolean | Whether the todo has been completed |\n| `userId` | integer | ID of the user the todo belongs to |\n\n**Example Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"todos\": [\n    { \"id\": 1, \"todo\": \"Do something nice for someone you care about\", \"completed\": false, \"userId\": 152 },\n    { \"id\": 2, \"todo\": \"Memorize a poem\", \"completed\": true, \"userId\": 13 }\n  ]\n}\n```"
					},
					"response": []
				},
